title: VCs deploy 'kingmaking' strategy to crown AI winners in their infancy | TechCrunch
description: While VCs have long used big investments to spur category winners, they are taking this strategy to new extremes.
content: In early October, DualEntry, an AI enterprise resource planning (ERP) startup, announced a $90 million Series A round led by Lightspeed and Khosla Ventures, valuing the one-year-old business at $415 … [+4042 chars]
